

The press center for the fifth round of the six-party talks on the Korean Peninsula nuclear issue will be open to reporters from 8:00 a.m. Wednesday morning.

The new round of talks, involving China, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, the United States, Republic of Korea, Russia and Japan, is to start on Wednesday morning at the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse, the venue of previous rounds of talks.

The press center, located at the Diaoyutai Hotel, will be available to reporters from home and abroad from 8:00 to 21:00 everyday. It is equipped with ten desktop computers and four wires for broadband Internet, as well as facilities such as telephones, printers, duplicating machines and fax machines.

More than 100 overseas correspondents have registered to report the talks, sources said.

